5:
Man, there's no breaking this... Are
we sure this is just ice?
8:
It must be extremely advanced ice
magic... Yet I've never met any
sorcerer capable of such feats.
10:
There's no mistake, the culprit must
be close by.
13:
They took down the Guild Knights
too, right?
16:
Yes. Some of the Guild's finest
warriors, too. They're hard-pressed
to deal with this matter on their
own—so much so that they're
begging adventurers for aid.
19:
To make matters worse, no one's
found a way to break the spell
either...
30: Hey, Light, that guy's using ice magic!
33:
This is bad... That man has an
Oculus! If he spots us—
40:
Show yourselves. If you bear no ill
intent, you will comply with my
request.
43:
But if you insist upon lurking in the
shadows, I will take that as a threat...
47:
Tch, this some kind of joke? It's clear
as day this guy's out for blood.
60:
All right. No more lurking. Happy?
Now, are you gonna come with me,
or are we gonna have to do this the
hard way?
63:
Forgive me, but I cannot be caught
just yet. There's still much I must do.
65:
I'm afraid I shall have to force my
way through.
69: Fine by me! Bring it on, you—
74:
Hello, my name is Stella. What's
yours?
78:
The hell are you doing, Stella?! Get
back!
81:
He said we should comply with his
request if we bore no ill intent.
85:
Now it is your turn to show us you
are not a threat.
90:
My apologies. It seems there has
been some sort of
misunderstanding.
92:
Your courage is commendable,
young lady... Perhaps we could chat
for a moment? That includes your
friends in the tree.
97:
My name is Reylas Oraclus. I am
currently traveling through Palpebra
on a mission. I arrived here earlier
this morning.
100:
It seems I mistook you for a group of
mountain bandits. My apologies.
104:
N-no, we're the ones who should
apologize. We're sorry for the mix-up.
107:
Pay it no mind. You're looking for a
sorcerer that encases people in ice.
It's perfectly logical to suspect me.
112:
Reylas, you wouldn't happen to have
any relation to these attacks, would
you?
114:
Your right eye is an Oculus, correct?
Those possess potent magic, and
are able to freeze opponents with
just a glare.
116:
Whoever did this bears the same
power as you—and appeared in the
exact places you have. Surely that
cannot be a coincidence.
120:
I do not wish to lead you astray. As
you've correctly inferred, the culprit
is using an Oculus. Specifically, my
left eye.
127:
Strictly speaking, the only thing
stolen was its power as an Oculus. I
am currently on a quest to take
back that power.
130:
I will say this now: Forget everything
you heard and stay far away from
this case.
133:
Those frozen by the Oculus can only
be thawed by its owner. Even my
clan did not escape an icy
entrapment.
136:
I assume you do not have the
means to combat an Oculus. Am I
correct?
139: Well, we cannot just stand here and—
142: I will stop the culprit's rampage.
145:
I just wish to avoid involving others.
The fewer victims, the better. Please
understand.
150:
N-no, you've got it all wrong! Please
listen to—
154:
I was wrong to use my power so
carelessly. Then I have no choice
but to—
158:
H-hold on! He's not the man you're
looking for!
161:
Um, thank you so much for helping
me!
165:
I do not know what would have
happened if you had not stepped in.
You have my thanks.
168:
It's fine. The Guild helps us out a lot,
so we have a responsibility towards
them, you know?
174: To be quite honest, not well.
177:
All I wish to do is take responsibility
for my mistakes, but I can't even
accomplish that. How pathetic.
186:
I believe I told you I won't see any
more innocent people hurt.
190:
Well, yeah, but we've got intel from
the Guild, you know. That might help
you out.
192:
Wouldn't there be less victims if you
accepted our help instead of going
at it alone?
195: Well... You do have a point...
205:
Oh dear... You can be quite
assertive, can't you?
208:
That being said... I humbly accept
your generosity.
211:
I look forward to our journey
together.
